    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fastenings for French or casement doors that consist of long rods, often hooked, at the top and bottom of the sash and that operate with a handle in the center. These use a round or square bar, distinguished from the half-round bar of a cremorne bolt.</Note_Text>
